The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Expansion takes Park to Pune
                                                                                                               Expansion takes Park to Pune
          A STAFF REPORTER                                                SUCCESS STORY		    
	Calcutta, Feb. 19: Apeejay Surrendra Park Hotels Ltd will invest Rs 300 crore to set up a five-star hotel in Pune as part of its expansion plans in the country.        
	The hospitality major has acquired 90,000 sq ft of land at Wakewadi, Pune, for the project.         
	I am delighted to announce this acquisition in Pune, which is one of the fastest growing mini metros in the country. The property will add to our chain of boutique hotels and will bear our unique trademark in design and innovation, said Priya Paul, chairperson of Apeejay Surrendra Park Hotels.        
	The Pune property is estimated to have a built-up area of 4,00,000 sq ft with 220 rooms, restaurants and entertainment facilities. It will be ready for the launch by 2010.        
	The hotelier also has properties in Bangalore, Chennai, New Delhi, Calcutta, Navi Mumbai and Visakhapatnam.        
	A 280-room hotel and retail project in Hyderabad is under construction and will start operations in 2009.         
	The group has also acquired land in Jaipur for a five-star property.        
	In July last year, the company raised $55 million from its stake sale to Credit Suisseto increase its footprint in the country.        
	The real estate fund of Credit Suisse was reported to have picked up to 15 per cent in the Park Hotels chain.                                                                                                                                        
